en_713611_0	The annual Inter Regiment Boxing Tournament that went on for 4 days (12 - 15 Feb) at Panagoda Indoor Stadium crowned Vijayabahu Infantry Regiment (VIR) boxers as overall Champions for the third consecutive year during the finals on Friday (15).
en_713611_1	Lieutenant General Mahesh Senanayake, Commander of the Army attached importance to the event by being a witness to the finals at the invitation of Major General Rukmal Dias, Chairman, Sri Lanka Army Boxing Committee.
en_713611_2	VIR boxers giving a tough resistance to the rival Sri Lanka Armoured Corps (SLAC) boxers grabbed 4 Gold medals, 1 Silver medal and 1 Bronze medal as the final score board clicked.
en_713611_3	Out of 10 VIR boxers who competed in the tournament, 4 boxers emerged winners in 60 kg, 75 kg, 69 kg and 64 kg categories and won Gold medals.
en_713611_4	VIR claimed the championship for the unbroken 3rd year and made a historic record in the field of sports.
en_713611_5	Private K.M.S.P Konara of 24 VIR (Gold - 60kg), Private D.S Dasanayake of 23 VIR (Gold - 75 kg), Private A.L.S.D Perera of 5 VIR (Gold - 69 kg) Private P.S.P Fernando of 24 VIR (Gold - 64 kg), Private P.M Wijewickrama of 10 (V) VIR (Silver - 81 kg) and Private N.A.Y.M Nissanka of 5 VIR (Bronze - 91 kg) were among the top achievers in the VIR.
en_713611_6	Sri Lanka Armoured Corps (SLAC) with 1 Gold, 1 Silver and 3 Bronze medals were adjudged the first runner-up while the 3rd place went to Sri Lanka Light Infantry (SLLI) boxing team who won 1 Gold, 1 Silver and 2 Bronze medals.
en_713611_7	Gunner H.M.L.P Jayawardene of SLAC was selected as the Best boxer and Corporal P.P.S Siriwardane of SLAC was rated the Best loser.
en_713611_8	Lieutenant General Mahesh Senanayake as the Chief Guest gave away trophies and awards to the winners at the end of the finals.
en_713611_9	Major General Ajith Kariyakarawana, Deputy Chief of Staff and Colonel of the Regiment, VIR, Major General Rukmal Dias, Chairman, Sri Lanka Army Boxing Committee and Commandant, Sri Lanka Army Volunteer Force, Major General Sathyapriya Liyanage, Commander, Security Forces - West, Major General Anura Sudasingha, Director General Army Sports Board, Major General Jagath Gunawardena, Master General Ordinance and Colonel of the Regiment, Corps of Engineers Services, Brigadiers and several Senior Officers were present during the finals.
